{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 Feature: BWell Testing task\line
  As a User who is interested in CMS platforms\line
  I want to create Appointments\line
  So that I can plan my activities at "http://login.myappcms.com/build"\line
    \line
Background:\line
  Given the user is on the "http://login.myappcms.com/" home page\line
  And they type "CMS Demo Account" as the App Name\line
  And they type "demo@diyappdesigner.com" as the Email address\line
  And they type "demo123" as the Password\line
  When they click on Sign in button\line
  Then they should see the CMS Demo Account Dashboard\line
    \line
Scenario: User can see Add Service Appointment form\line
  Given the user is on the CMS Demo Account Dashboard page\line
  When the user clicks on the Appointments item in the sidebar\line
  And the user clicks on the Services sub-item below the Appointments item\line
  And the user clicks on the Add button under the Services tab\line
  Then the user can see the Services addition form\line
    \line
Scenario Outline: User Adds Service Appointment\line
  Given the user is on the Services addition form\line
  And the user has clicked the Add button\line
  When the user enters the value "<value>" in the field "<fieldname>"\line
  And the user clicks on the Save button\line
  Then the Service Name, Service Description, Duration, Price and Opening Hours should be evident in the Services list\line
  \line
  Examples: Fields\line
    | fieldname | value |\line
    | Service Name | With a Smile |\line
    | Service Description | It's our middle name |\line
    | Duration | 1:10 |\line
    | Price | 20.00 |\line
    | Opening Hours | 08:00 - 17:00 |\line
    | Image | https://www.freepnglogos.com/uploads/cucumber-png/cucumber-slice-hydrate-photo-pixabay-23.png |\line
    | Column7 | Collum 7 |\line
    | Column8 | Call 'em 8 |\line
    | Sheet1 | Sheets to the wind |\line
    \line
Scenario: User can Update Services Appointment entry\line
  Given the user is on the Services list pane\line
  When the user clicks the Edit (pencil) icon for the previously-created appointment\line
  And the user changes the Service Name to "Testing Services"\line
  And the user clicks on the Save button\line
  Then the updated Service Name "Testing Services" should be evident in the Services list\line
    \line
Scenario: User can Cancel an Update Services Appointment entry\line
  Given the user is on the Services list pane\line
  When the user clicks the Edit (pencil) icon for the previously-created appointment\line
  And the user changes the Service Name from "Testing Services" to "Service Not Saved"\line
  And the user clicks on the Cancel button\line
  Then the Service Name "Testing Services" should still be evident in the Services list\line
    \line
Scenario: User can Delete Services Appointment entry\line
  Given the user is on the Services list pane\line
  When the user clicks the Delete (trashcan) icon for the previously-created appointment "Testing Services"\line
  And the user clicks Yes in response to "Are you sure you want to remove this item?"\line
  Then the previously-created Service Name "Testing Services" should be removed from the Services list\par}
